A Development (Dev) subscription in Azure is used for building, testing, and experimenting with applications. It is typically used by developers and is separate from production environments.

This separation ensures that development activities do not affect live applications.

For example, developers can deploy new features, test APIs, and experiment with configurations in the Dev subscription without impacting users.

A real-life use case is agile development. Teams continuously develop and test features in the Dev environment before promoting them to higher environments.

Another example is learning and experimentation, where engineers can safely explore Azure services without risking production stability.

Dev subscriptions are essential for maintaining a safe and controlled development workflow.
